@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(SEQ-VALIDATE-CLI, 0015)
' @id(SEQ-VALIDATE-CLI)
' @ref(USE-VALIDATE-CLI)
' @desc(SEQ-VALIDATE-CLI, "Current flow for `mdd validate`: the Commands::Validate { json } arm in mdd-cli/src/main.rs calls Project::discover then Project::validate(), which walks both sides and returns ValidationReport { ok, errors, warnings }. With --json the arm prints serde_json::to_string_pretty over a slim json!({ok, errors, warnings}) view (the ModelRegistry field is omitted); otherwise it prints each error/warning line and a VALIDATION: PASSED/FAILED summary. It calls std::process::exit(1) when !report.ok and returns 0 otherwise; warnings never change the exit code. No call to Project::review().")
' Current sequence (cycle 0015): validate subcommand surfacing the
' already-tested Project::validate engine, text and --json modes.
title mdd validate — deterministic structural gate (current)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev
participant "mdd validate [--json]\n(Commands::Validate)" as Cli
participant "Project::validate()" as Engine
participant "ValidationReport\n{ok, errors, warnings}" as Report

Dev -> Cli : mdd validate [--json]
Cli -> Engine : validate() over current/ + objective/
Engine --> Cli : ValidationReport { ok, errors, warnings }
alt --json
  Cli --> Dev : slim {ok, errors, warnings} JSON (registry excluded)
else text (default)
  Cli --> Dev : error/warning lines + VALIDATION: PASSED/FAILED
end
Cli --> Dev : exit 1 if !ok, else 0 (warnings never block)
@enduml
